President Donald J. Trump and Prime Minister Theresa May of the United Kingdom met to discuss joint efforts in defeating ISIS and other jihadist terrorist organizations in Syria and Iraq. They also talked about addressing Iran's behavior in the Middle East and flaws in the Iran nuclear deal. The leaders committed to expanding trade between the two countries and promoting fair and reciprocal trade practices globally. Additionally, they discussed plans for a working visit to London in the near future and emphasized the strength of the "special relationship" between the United States and the United Kingdom.